notes: 12th Men: IJ Harvey (Australia) and Javed Omar (Bangladesh)
Khalid Mashud was struck on the thumb by a Brett Lee delivery, while he continued his innings he was unable to field in the Australian innings. Hannan Sarkar kept wicket.

milestones.description: This is the lowest match aggregate (212) involving teams Australia & Bangladesh in ODIs

stories.title: Australian pace attack too hot for Bangladesh
stories.summary: Bangladesh's batsmen found the pace of Brett Lee and Jason Gillespie too hot to handle, as Australia eased to an eight-wicket win in the first one-day international of the three-match series
